		<a href="MB_editmsg.asp?FID=62&FN=Druid&SID=7&SN=EverQuest&TID=418266&TN=Charging+for+tp+%21%21%21%21&CAT=Classes&SURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Eeverlore%2Ecom&MSID=418269&PL=4">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/edit.gif" border="0" alt="Edit/Delete Message" width="18" height="13"></a>
		
		</font>
		<hr size="1">I don't charge for SoW and I never have. I have accepted donations for it when I first got it, but since level 16 or so I haven't accepted payment. It is quick casting and requires little mana once you get up a few levels.<P>Teleports are a far different thing. I have done many free ports but it just depends on the situation and what I am doing. If I am headed to that zone anyway, I love giving a free ride to someone if they are there and ready to go. I never respond to WTB auctions unless an amount is mentioned.<P>The thing about porting people is that it is so darn time consuming. You have to meet them, mem spell, port them, mem spell, gate back. If you were in a zone without a ring, then you have to travel back to where ever you were. On top of that, it takes 300 mana to port and 75 to 150 to get back.<P>Rreku<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
	</td>
