		<hr size="1">here is my opinon as a lev 19 druid.  I will usually give sow free if I have extra mana and they are near me.  If they ask for sow and are in zone not near me I will offer to sow for donation (whatever they give me).  I have no problem paying folks 10 pp for a port.  20 pp is too high I think, especially for us low level folks.  I barely had the 120 plat it took to get my new spells at 19. (self port YEAH).  The very first time I got a port was when a friend and I wanted to go to freeport for the first time.  We were both level 7 and where veery poor.  I had saved up about 3 plat and we were rdy to travel.  We saw a druid saying "plane leaving fro freeport area in 5 min" so we ran to the spot he mentioned.  He kindly asked us to pay first becasue people sometimes go LD.   I said that we had saved up 3 plat and asked how much a port cost.  He then switched to tell and asked me how long I had been playing.  I told him this was my first char and I had played about a week or so.  He said that 1gp per person would cover it.  He then ported us without anything further.  Later when I found out ports are usually 10 plat each I realised what a nice person we had met.  By charging us 1gp per person he made us feel like we were paying our way, without taking much of our money.  I try to help out those who need it and usually those that have the money will donate more then I would have asked any way.<P>------------------<BR>Lysear level 14 mage <BR>The power to summon the elements is the power to banish your enemies.<P>19th level druid Keeth Bertoxx<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
