		<hr size="1">One of the most wonderful things about having the ability to cast SoW is that it gives you the ability to really make someone's day.  I often spend an entire batch of mana running around newbie areas (usually near Kelethin) casting SoW on people who are bashing their way through their first 5 lvl's.  Often they don't know what they've received until long after I've run off... it makes me happy thinking of their face when the realize how fast they're running.<P>That said, like many others here, I never advertise or expect payment for SoW.  If someone offers or simply gives me money before I run off then I am more than happy to take it.  As you all know, our spells are expensive and this extra money helps alot.  The first day I reached lvl 14 and hurriedly purchases SoW a wonderfully twink'd paladin sent me a tell "I'll give you 20pp for a sow."  Needless to say, I was broke and ran TOP SPEED to him.  I was ecstatic!  I told him "if you ever need another SoW, send me a tell, I'll run across the continent..."  An hour later, he gave me another 20pp... <P>So, sure I believe it's perfectly ethical to take money for SoW and teleport as they save people precious time and they are often more than happy to pay for it.  Afterall, we're not enchanting +6 wisdom rings and selling them for 200pp... A little extra money never hurts.<P>Adaiz Goodspeed<BR>Wood Elf Druid of 25th<BR>Tribunal<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
