		<hr size="1">I am just starting a Druid, and decided to look at this board for advice.  My only other character is a 15th Level Human Paladin, and while I really enjoy playing as a Paladin I wanted to branch out a bit and understand better the other classes and what they bring to the game.  That said, the thing that strikes me as odd about this post is that Druids are so generous about SoWing and other buffs, despite the fact that some of the people are so damned needy or rude about requesting buffs.  I have never begged for a SoW and probably never will; however, I have received several for helping druids or just out of their kindness.  I just wanted to share with you my perspective as a non-Druid and a Paladin; we don't need the buffs if we play well.  When I solo I spend most of my time lumbering along the landscape, keeping a look out so I don't get ambushed by HGs, SGs, Specters and the like.  I use different camera views to make sure that no one sneaks up on me, and if they do I plant myself close to a zone so I can lumber back to safety.  This and other techniques ensure that I don't have to rely on others to have fun and continue to advance.  But when I want to tackle something tougher than what I can solo I group.  Those people out there who constantly yell for SoW and other buffs are trying to reap the benefits of grouping without paying the costs - sharing loot, experience, etc.  As a druid I will probably decline to buff anyone if they are begging for it…<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
